        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2646301385" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7495439744317152515">An important book-- and in light of today&apos;s report that ocean waters are heating up even faster than first thought, <br/>it takes on more importance. The author digs into databanks from climate studies around the globe and makes projections on what the specific on-the-ground effects will be of rising global temperatures. The six degrees by the way, is centigrade, not fahrenheit. If you&apos;re interested in climate science and some of the gritty specifics of what future generations will be dealing with- I</span>
  <span id="freeText7495439744317152515" style="display:none">An important book-- and in light of today's report that ocean waters are heating up even faster than first thought, <br />it takes on more importance. The author digs into databanks from climate studies around the globe and makes projections on what the specific on-the-ground effects will be of rising global temperatures. The six degrees by the way, is centigrade, not fahrenheit. If you're interested in climate science and some of the gritty specifics of what future generations will be dealing with- I recommend this book highly. </span>
